0 COLOUR COLOR ANSI~
Syntax: color    Toggles color mode on/off

To use colors you use the 'escape character' which is the left
handed brace, '{{', followed by the letter of the color you
want. Remember that it looks better if you finish the line with
whatever color the channel would normally be in. Examples below.

                {r{{r     red       {R{{R     b. red
                {c{{c     cyan      {C{{C     b. cyan
                {g{{g     green     {G{{G     b. green
                {y{{y     yellow    {Y{{Y     b. yellow
                {b{{b     blue      {B{{B     b. blue
                {w{{w     white     {W{{W     b. white
                {m{{m     purple    {M{{M     b. purple
                {K{{K     black     {x{{x     reset color
                {{{{      {{ character

EXAMPLE: {mLope gossips '{ghello,{r world{m!'{x is better than
         {mLope gossips '{ghello,{r world!'{x

        Color is written by Lope (ant@solace.mh.se)
~

