-1 WAR WARRIOR~
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
CLASS| Warrior        |
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION: The warrior class is the most basic fighting class available.
Their battle training along with high strength and high hitpoints make them
very formidable in hand to hand combat.  Warriors train in the art of multiple
attacks.  Some master the art of second attack and if experienced enough,
master third attack.  Along with this training in multiple attacks, a warrior
is trained in making each hit count.  Enhanced damage is available to only the
learned.  Toweard the defense side of the warrior, skills of parry, rescue,
and bash door allow the warrior to ward off attacks, rush to the aid of fellow
comrades, and open doors rather barbarically.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
SUITABLE      | Warriors work well with Humans, elves, ogres, dwarves, 
RACES         | lizardman, demon, halfling, ghoul, minotaur, troll, and 
              | tabaxi.  The other races have much trouble learning the art of
              | war.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
~

-1 CLE CLERIC~
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
CLASS| Cleric         |
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION:  The cleric class is a 'spellcasting' class devoted primarity
toward defense.  A deity gives the cleric spells in the curing, warding,
and protective divinities.  Clerics being of a defensive nature fare poorly
in the art of mortal combat.  They much prefer to be civil servents to 
society or doctors to their comrades in arms.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
RACES         | Dawrves, humans, elves, and elders seem to create the best
              | clerics, while most other races have a harder time with 
              | mastering the art of healing.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
~

-1 MAG MAGE MAGIC MAGIC-USER 'MAGIC USER'~
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
CLASS| Mage           |
-----+--------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION:  The mage class is a 'spellcasting' class devoted primarily
toward control over the elements.  The universe contains an unmeasured power
the mage taps into to influence the world.  Mage spells are devoted to the 
invoking, hermetic, and combative nature.  Mages fare a little better than
their cleric counterparts in spell-casting combat, though, they would much
rather stand back and roast their enemies with spells than stand melee.
-------------+------------------------------------------------------------------
SUITABLE     | Mages work well with any race that does not have a wisdom or
RACES        | intelligence hinderance.
-------------+------------------------------------------------------------------
~

-1 THI THIEF~
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
CLASS| Thief          |
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION:  The thief class can be characterized as a warrior who dropped
out of school to persue more "profitable" means of living.  These wirey
persons have physical endurance slightly less than that of a warrior, but are
much more agile.  Whereas a warrior uses well places weapon slashes, a thief
sneaks to disarm his opponent.  Thieves also excel in the art of stealth.
An unwary opponent might not detet a thief until a backstab is attemted.  To
achieve success in this, the skills 'sneak' and 'hide' are learned.  With a
thief's pick lock and poison weapon skills, a thief also makes the perfect
assassin for a political powerhouse.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
SUITABLE      | Humans, elves, halflings, and shadows make excellent thieves.
RACES         | Ogres, trolls, elders have a hard time handling the
              | profession.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
~

-1 PSIONICIST PSI~
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
CLASS| Psionicist     |
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION: The psionicist is a 'spellcasting' class similar to mages and
clerics but with several important differences.  Where a mage's power comes
from harnessing external energies present in all matter, and a cleric's power
comes from his or her deity, the psionic derives all of his or her power
from him or herself.  The psionic harnesses, shapes, and utilizes the natural
forces within his or her own being.  As a result, many of the devotions
that a psionic can practice are strictly personal in effect, and cannot be
used on others.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
SUITABLE      | Illithid, humans and demons make for excellent psionics,
RACES         | while most other races have a hard time (if even enough
              | intelligence) to master the psionic class.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
~

