0 RANGER~
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
CLASS| Ranger         |
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION:  The ranger class is a class devoted primarily towards hand-to-
hand combat.  The ranger, much like the druid, has a powerful affiliation with
nature and recieves limited spells from the druid class repetoire.  Though
the ranger does not have as many multiple attacks as the warrior, his
spellcasting abilities make the ranger a formidable foe.  Few can best a 
prepared ranger.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
SUITABLE      | Dwarves, elves, humans and lizardmen make for the best
RACES         | rangers, while most other races either find it more difficult
              | or do not care for nature as the ranger does.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
~

0 BARD~
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
CLASS| Bard           |
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION: Bards are travelling minstels, collecting takes and lore wherever
they happen to be.  They are extremely curious and have a deep wanderlust.
They usually form their stories into songs.  Bards rarely stay in one place
too long.  On their many journeys, bards have become a jack of all trades,
but masters of none.  They possess many skills and spells from the different
classes gathered as they wander the Realms.  Bards posses the gift for words
and singing.  Their voices and songs possess great powers.  They sing their
songs in perparation of battle, during battle, and after to protect, destroy,
and heal.
 
See help 'sing' for more details.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
SUITABLE      | Elves and humans seem to be the only races that possess the
RACES         | charm, singing talent, and the vigor that it takes to be a 
              | bard.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
~

0 DRUID~
-----+--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------
CLASS| Druid        |
-----+--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION:  Druids are a powerful nature based class.  Their intimate
knowledge of the land allows them to draw magic from it.  They use nature
as their ally, controlling it and shaping it to fit their needs.  Druids are
the priests of nature, and the guardians and protectors of the forests.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
SUITABLE      | Minotaurs, pixies, elders, elves, and humans make for good
RACES         | races, while all others cannot seem to grasp the control
              | of nature needed to become a druid.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
~

0 PALADIN~
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
CLASS| Paladin        |
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION:  The paladin is an incredible fighter that lives by his deeds.
As strong as a warrior, the paladin fares well in battle.  His skills are not
only in the art of war, but in the art of healing.  With luck, tales of a 
paladin's deeds will live long after that paladin has ceased to exist. 
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
SUITABLE      | Minotaur, lizardmen, and humans are the only races that are
RACES         | skilled in the ways of a paladin.  All other races do not have
              | the paticular heart, and nature that it takes to live the life
              | of a paladin.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
~

0 VAMPIRE~
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
CLASS| Vampire        |
-----+----------------+---------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION:  The vampire is a class that owns the night.  Their spells are
focused on draining the life from the living.  They get their power from the
blood of others.  Vampires possess the spell 'Dark Blessing' which
greatly improves their hitpoints and damage roll.  Vampires are also powerful
fighters who can dual wield.  A vampire, however strong, has a huge 
disadvantage from the sunlight, and must be indoors to be safe from the suns'
harmful light during the daylight hours.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
SUITABLE      | Shadows, trolls, minotaurs, and demons
RACES         | make the best vampires.  Humans, elves, dwarves, and pixies
              | have a harder time as mastering the skills and spells of a
              | vampires life, but still manage.
--------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
 
~

102 NEWCORPSE~
Syntax: newcorpse <player> Syntax: newcorpse <player> <corpse #>
Newcorpse allows you to recreate a corpse for a player who has lost thiers. 
The player must be online in order for the corpse to be recreated.  The 5
most recent corpses will be saved.  Typing newcorpse <player> will display a
list of corpses and number of items each corpse contains The corpses will be
flagged as valid or invalid.  DO NOT recreate an invalid corpse.  The
newcorpse routine is fairly intelligent and will not save corpses containing
only one item.  Therefore if the player has died trying to get his original
corpse, and has only a light source, that corpse will not be saved.  Once
the apporiate corpses to be recreated is decided upon , typing newcorpse
<player> <corpse #> will recreate the corpse.  The corpse will be recreated
in the room in which you issued the command.  
 
~

