1 AUTOQUEST~
Autoquesting is for every level and there are certain rules and
commands to know about.   You have to be at a Quest Master mob to use most
the available commands.  

QUEST INFO: This will tell you what you are currently questing for.
QUEST TIME: Displays the amount of time you have left to complete your current
            quest or the amount of time until you can quest again if you just
            quested.
QUEST POINTS: This will tell you the amount of quest points you have so far.
QUEST REQUEST: This allows you to -request- an autoquest. The Quest Master
               will then see if it has a quest to give you.
QUEST COMPLETE: Once you've completed a quest, return to the Quest Master
                who assigned you the quest, and type QUEST COMPLETE.
QUEST LIST: This lists the available items you can buy with your quest points. 
            You must be at a Quest Master to list or buy items also.
QUEST BUY: To buy an item type QUEST BUY <item>.
QUEST AREA: When you are assigned a quest, you may type QUEST AREA to see what
            area your quest is in.

 
Autoquests are random, and chosen suitable to your level. Sometimes you will
get a quest to kill a mob, or a quest to find an object. If you are assigned an
object quest, the object is placed in the room of a suitable mob according to 
your level. You must go get the object and return to the Quest Master and
type QUEST COMPLETE.  He will then take the object from you and reward you with
quest points.
 
If you are assigned a mob quest, you must go find the mob and kill it, then 
return to the Quest Master and type QUEST COMPLETE.  The mob you are to kill
will have a [TARGET] flag and while you are questing you will have a [QUESTING]
flag.  
 
 --- Before you begin questing, make sure you read HELP AUTOQUEST RULES ---
 
The amount of time you are given for a quest is random, and can range anywhere
from 10-30 minutes.  Once you have completed a quest, you must wait 30 minutes 
-REAL- time before you can autoquest again.  If you request a quest and the
Quest Master doesn't have a quest for you, you must wait 10 minutes before
trying to quest again.
 
The points you gain while questing are saved every time you log off, but don't
last forever.  Each ten levels you lose any quest points you might of gained,
for example at level 10 you would be back at 0 quest points.  So quest lots and
spend your quest points! Don't forget to read HELP AUTOQUEST RULES. Anyone
who doesn't abide by the rules will have to deal with the consequences. We want
this to be enjoyable for everyone.
~

