-1 LAWFUL_GOOD~
Characters of this alignment believe that an orderly, strong, organized
government and a strong society can work to make life better for all people.
To ensure the quality of life, laws must be created.  Therefore, people of
this alignment strive for those things that will bring the greatest benifit
to the most people and cause the least harm.
~

-1 LAWFUL_NEUTRAL~
Orders and organizations are paramount for people of this type.  Whether the
order come from tryranny or benevolence, it doesnt matter.  The benifits
of organization and regimentation outweigh any moral questions raised by
their actions.
~

-1 LAWFUL_EVIL~
These people believe in using society and laws as a benifit to themselves.
Lawful evil characters obey orders out of fear of punishment.  Because they
may may be forced to honor an unfavorable contract or oath they have made,
lawful evil characters are very weary of giving their word.  Once given,
they break their word only within the legal system.
~

-1 NEUTRAL_GOOD~
These characters believe that a balance of forces is important, but that the
laws of chaos and order do not moderate the need for good.  Since the 
universe is vast and contains many different creatures and many different
goals, a determined persuit for good will not matter.  If supporting good
means that you must uphold law, then so be it.  If supporting good means
overthrowing society, then so be it.
~

-1 TRUE_NEUTRAL~
These characters believe in the ultimate forces of balance and they refuse to
see actions as good or evil.  Since the majority of the people in the world
make judgements, these characters are few and far between.  True neutrals
